<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>427970</id>
    <title>Bookmark deleted when right-clicking shortcut toolbar button and pressing 't'</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.13) Gecko/20080311 Firefox/2.0.0.13
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.8.1.13) Gecko/20080311 Firefox/2.0.0.13</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">When on a web page, and i right-click a link to get an options menu, the link for Open Link in New Tab is 'T' and Open Link in New Window is 'W'.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">However, when right-clicking on a shortcut in the Bookmarks Toolbar, the action for the 'T' key is "Delete".</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">The result is that I often accidentally delete my shortcuts from the toolbar instead of opening that shortcut in a new tab.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">1 Right-click on a link in the shortcut toolbar</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.3">2 Press 'T' on the keyboard</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.4">3 Watch your shortcut disappear</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.5">Actual Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.6">The shortcut got deleted</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">Expected Results:  
Same behaviour is "Open in a new Tab" context menu for a link on a web page</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="8">
            <sentence id="8.1">One would expect the same hot-keys in the context menu on a web page and in the shortcut menu, IE  'W' for open in new window and 'T' for open in new tab.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="9">
            <sentence id="9.1">I realize that 'T' this is a standard windows key for "Cut", so perhaps changing the context menu the web link context menu to 'N' for new window and 'W' for new tab would be the alternative solution.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
